Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Halve the @baking potato{2} lengthways and pop them onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle
with @oil{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Rub the oil over the potatoes,
then lay them cut-side down on the baking tray.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until tender and a knife slips in
easily, ~{30-40%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once
hot, add the @chorizo{60%g} and stir-fry for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @British beef mince{240%g} to the chorizo and continue to cook until
browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break the mince up as it cooks, then
drain and discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after
handling raw mince. The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more, then stir in the
@tomato passata{1}, @chipotle paste{20%g}, @beef stock paste{10%g},
@sugar{1/2%tsp} and @water{100%ml} for the sauce.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer, stirring occasionally, until
the sauce has thickened, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, cut the @lime{1} into wedges.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh
out into a #bowl{}.

Add a squeeze of lime juice and a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Mash the avocado
with a #fork{} and mix well.

Taste and add more salt, pepper and lime juice if needed, then set your guacamole
aside.

Cut the @medium tomato{2} into 1cm chunks and pop into another bowl.

Drizzle over a little oil, squeeze in some lime juice and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Set the salsa aside.

Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Once the chilli has thickened and the mince is cooked, season with salt and pepper
and squeeze in a little lime juice. Taste and season again if needed.

When everything's ready, transfer the baked potatoes to your #serving plates{}, cut-side
up.

Spoon your beef and chorizo chilli on top (reheat first if needed), then scatter
over the cheese.

Top with some dollops of @soured cream{75%g} and guacamole, then spoon over the
tomato salsa to finish.

Serve your ultimate loaded jacky p with any remaining lime wedges alongside for
squeezing over. Enjoy!